    <fr:title text="Closure of regular languages under complementation › "><fr:link href="jms-018F.xml" title="Closure of regular languages under complementation" addr="jms-018F" type="local">Closure of <fr:link href="jms-017Y.xml" title="Regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular languages</fr:link> under complementation</fr:link> › </fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-017Y.xml" title="Regular language" addr="jms-017Y" type="local">regular language</fr:link>, and so by <fr:link href="jms-018B.xml" title="Kleene’s theorem" addr="jms-018B" type="local">Kleene’s theorem</fr:link> we have some <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L=\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We define a new <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lnot {M}]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (\lnot {M}\right )\mathclose {}} = \Sigma ^\star \setminus  L]]></fr:tex> by setting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lnot {M}]]></fr:tex> to have the same states, transition function, and starting state as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> but with the opposite set of accepting states:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  F_{\lnot {M}} = Q_{M}\setminus F_{M}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>The desired property of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lnot {M}]]></fr:tex> is immediate.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
