            <fr:title text="Regular language">Regular <fr:link href="jms-016M.xml" title="Formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">language</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:link href="jms-016M.xml" title="Formal language" addr="jms-016M" type="local">formal language</fr:link> is called <fr:em><fr:strong>regular</fr:strong></fr:em> if it is equal to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {L}{\mathopen {}\left (R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:link href="jms-0179.xml" title="Regular expressions (abstract syntax)" addr="jms-0179" type="local">regular expression</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
